parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility during inclement weather, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working
work intermittently
or become stuck in a vertical position; wipers may not turn off when switched off; wipers may work at regular speed when in the intermittent position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window motor can cause inconvenience and discomfort, and may lead to safety issues if the windows are stuck in a position that obstructs the driver's view.
symptoms: Power windows fail to roll up or down
work intermittently
or become stuck in a position; windows may not respond to the switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of safety issues, including fires, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Switches burn or smoke
electrical components fail
and systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal pulsates or drops to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the ABS light on the dashboard illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake fluid leaks onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotor can cause the brakes to vibrate, pulsate, or fail, leading to extended stopping distances and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal vibrates or pulsates
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brake rotor is excessively worn or warped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the brake pedal and accelerator pedal can cause the driver's foot to accidentally press the accelerator pedal while braking, leading to unintended acceleration and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver's foot accidentally presses the accelerator pedal while braking
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the loss of power steering and brake control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loss of power steering
stiff or unresponsive steering
loss of brake control
inability to slow down or stop
grinding or screeching noise from the power steering pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydro boost system can cause the loss of power brakes and power steering, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loss of power brakes
loss of power steering
stiff or unresponsive steering
inability to slow down or stop
grinding or screeching noise from the power steering pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idler arm can cause the loss of power steering, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loss of power steering
stiff or unresponsive steering
clunking or grinding noise from the front suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Slipping or hesitation when shifting gears
loss of power
grinding or screeching noise from the transmission.
